# Project 2 — Credit Card Fraud Detection

## The business problem
A bank processes 1.3M credit card transactions.
Only 0.58% are fraudulent — but missing them costs millions.
Build a model that flags fraud in real time without blocking innocent customers.

## Dataset
- Source: Credit Card Transactions Fraud Detection (Kaggle — kartik2112)
- Training: 1,296,675 transactions | 7,506 fraud (0.58%)
- Test: 555,719 transactions | 2,145 fraud (0.39%)

## The core challenge — class imbalance
99.42% legitimate vs 0.58% fraud.
A model that predicts "not fraud" every time is 99.42% accurate — and useless.
Solution: scale_pos_weight = 172 (tells model to weight fraud 172x more heavily)

## Model
- Algorithm: XGBoost with scale_pos_weight=172
- Features: amount, category, hour, day of week, age, city population
- Key engineering: transaction hour extracted from timestamp

## Results

| Metric | Value | Plain English |
|--------|-------|---------------|
| AUC | 0.997 | Near-perfect fraud ranking |
| Recall | 96.4% | Catches 96 of every 100 fraud cases |
| Precision | 18.7% | Of flagged txns, 18.7% are real fraud |
| F1 | 0.313 | Aggressive model — high recall, lower precision |

## The confusion matrix

| | Predicted legit | Predicted fraud |
|--|--|--|
| **Actually legit** | 544,561 ✓ | 9,013 wrongly blocked |
| **Actually fraud** | 78 missed | 2,067 caught ✓ |

## Feature importance

| Feature | Importance | PM action |
|---------|-----------|-----------|
| Transaction amount | 59.3% | Flag transactions >$400 for confirmation |
| Hour of day | 20.3% | Extra friction 10pm–2am |
| Merchant category | 12.9% | Stricter rules for online shopping |
| Age | 4.4% | Low priority |
| City population | 2.0% | Not useful |

## Key findings

**Finding 1 — Online shopping is 10x riskier**
shopping_net: 1.76% fraud rate vs health_fitness: 0.15%

**Finding 2 — Fraudsters operate at night**
Hour 22–23: 2.86% fraud rate vs Hour 7: 0.13% — 22x difference

**Finding 3 — Fraudulent transactions are 8x larger**
Avg fraud: $531 vs avg legitimate: $67

## The PM tradeoff
9,013 innocent customers wrongly blocked to catch 2,067 fraudsters.
This is a business decision, not a model failure:
- Premium card brand → reduce weight, accept more fraud, protect experience
- Protection-first card → keep weight, maximise fraud caught

## Product roadmap

| Priority | Feature | Trigger | What to build |
|---------|---------|---------|--------------|
| P0 | Amount trigger | Transaction >$400 | Push notification: "Did you make this purchase?" |
| P0 | Night friction | 10pm–2am transaction | One-tap confirm in app |
| P1 | Category rules | Online shopping | Stricter model threshold |
| P2 | False positive recovery | Card wrongly blocked | One-tap unblock flow |

## Business impact
- Fraud caught value: **$1,092,113**
- Fraud missed value: $41,212
- ROI: 26x on fraud prevention vs missed fraud

